ow it can subordinate gender and sexuality to masculinity and heterosexual roles. Fregoso's self-reflexive approach to cultural politics embraces the movement for social justice and offers new insights into the ways that racial and gender differences are inscribed in cultural practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGroup identityzMexican-American Border Region. 0aMexican American womenxEthnic identity. 0aMexican American womenzMexican-American Border RegionxSocial conditions. 0aPopular culturezMexican-American Border Region. 0aWomen in motion pictures. 0aWomen in popular culturezMexican-American Border Region. 0aWomenzMexican-American Border RegionxSocial conditions. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh  aamerican borderlands.  achicanas.  achicano studies.  aciudad juarez.  acontemporary experience.  acultural politics.  acultural practices.  acultural studies.  adisappearances.  adomestic violence.  aethnographers.  aethnography.  afamily and identity.  afeminism.  afeminists.  agender and sexuality.  agender roles.  agender studies.  alatina experience.  alatinx studies.  amexicana representation.  amexicanas.  amexicans.  amurders.  anonfiction.  arace issues.  asocial identity.  asocial justice.  asocial studies.  asymbolism.  atransborder.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023890940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093728440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937284423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520937284/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY